10.00	Somatic_marker_hypothesis	Somatic marker hypothesis	When we make decisions, we must assess the incentive value of the choices available to us, using cognitive and emotional processes. When we face complex and conflicting choices, we may be unable to decide using only cognitive processes, which may become overloaded and unable to help us decide.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Ventromedial_prefrontal_cortex.png/220px-Ventromedial_prefrontal_cortex.png
